Federal Register: 232. Sodium o-phenylphenoxide (CAS No. 000132-27-4) (CERCLA; IARC) (Ref. 8). Sodium o-phenylphenoxide has been classified by IARC as a Group 2B compound; i.e., the substance is possibly carcinogenic in humans. EPA believes that there is sufficient evidence for listing sodium o-phenylphenoxide on EPCRA section 313 pursuant to EPCRA section 313(d)(2)(B) based on the carcinogenicity data for this chemical.
